<http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.sajb.2018.11.016>
    dc:creator "Jakoet, A.", "Magee, A. R.", "Mucina, L." ;
    dc:date "2019" ;
    dc:title "The pseudo-radiate buttons: A taxonomic revision of the Cotula turbinata group (Asteraceae; Anthemideae) and the description of two new species *" ;
    bibo:endPage "293" ;
    bibo:journal "South African Journal of Botany" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2019-01-01" ;
    bibo:startPage "282" ;
    bibo:volume "121" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496568>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496570>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496572>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496588> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496568>
    dc:description "Fig.1. Species of the Cotula turbinata group showing the main diagnostic characters.(A)The multi-nerved broad bracts found in all species in this group (from C.turbinata); (B) C.discolor; (C–D) Cotula turbinata,note the apical swelling of the peduncle;(E–H) Cotula calcicola, note the convex disc face (H) and size of the cypselae in the filiform florets (G); (I) Cotula pruinosa; (J–L) Cotula duckittiae, note the flat to concave disc face and the multiseriate pseudo-rays (K & L)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10496568/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496570>
    dc:description "Fig. 2. Floret variation and position in the Cotula turbinata group. (A) Diagram representing the positon of the different florets in a typical capitulum, with black circles representing the filiform florets, diamond shape representing the pseudo-ray florets and the white circles representing the disc florets; (B) typical filiform floret from C.pruinosa; (C) typical disc floret from C. duckittiae; (D-I) pseudo-ray florets in C. calcicola (D), C. discolor (E), C. duckittiae (F), C. perennans (G), C. pruinosa (H), and C. turbinata (I). Vouchers: (B) Jakoet & Magee 1111 (NBG); (C) Magee & Jakoet 1127 (NBG); (D) Magee & Jakoet 1138a (NBG); (E) Jakoet 54 (NBG); (F) Magee & Jakoet 1127 (NBG); (G) Esterhuysen 35120 (BOL); (H) Jakoet & Magee 1111 (NBG); (I) Magee & Jakoet 1114 (NBG). Scale: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10496570/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496572>
    dc:description "Fig.3. Cypsela variation in the Cotula turbinata group.(A) C.calcicola: (A1) cypsela of filiform floret; (A2) cypsela of disc floret;(B) C.discolor: (B1) cypsela of filiform floret; (B2) cypsela of disc floret;(C) C.duckittiae: (C1) cypsela of filiform floret;(C2) cypselaof disc floret;(D)C.perennans: (D1) cypsela of filiform floret;(D2) cypsela ofdisc floret;(E) C.pruinosa: (E1) cypsela of filiform floret;(E2) cypsela of disc floret;(F) C.turbinata: (F1) cypsela of filiform floret; (F2)cypsela of disc floret.Vouchers:(A1) & (A2) Magee & Jakoet 1138a (NBG);(B1) &(B2) Jakoet 54 (NBG);(C1) & (C2) Magee & Jakoet 1127 (NBG);(D1) Esterhuysen 33,481 (BOL);(D2) Esterhuysen 33693 (BOL) (E1) & (E2) Magee & Jakoet 1111 (NBG);(F1) & (F2) Magee & Jakoet1114 (NBG).Scale: 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10496572/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

